<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.220368>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A: Male holotype of Cyrtodactylus dati sp. nov. (ITBCZ 2375) in life; B: paratype of Cyrtodactylus dati sp. nov. (ITBCZ 2343) with newly regenerated tail; C: paratype of Cyrtodactylus dati sp. nov. (ITBCZ 2351), subadult male showing small light spots on its head; D: Paratype of Cyrtodactylus dati sp. nov. (ITBCZ 2350); subadult female showing some small light spots on its head." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/220368/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.220369>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Precloacal and femoral region of holotype of Cyrtodactylus dati sp. nov. showing the diastema between the precloacal and femoral pores (marked by blue dots), and the small subcaudal scales." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/220369/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.220370>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Preserved paratypes of Cyrtodactylus dati sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/220370/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

